#
# ENGINE_PIN — the exact vouchfx engine commit this samples repo builds against.
#
# What it pins
# ------------
# The first line is a full 40-character commit SHA on
# https://github.com/tomas-rampas/vouchfx. scripts/bootstrap.{ps1,sh} shallow-fetch
# exactly this commit into .vouchfx-src/ and build the engine CLI
# (src/Cli/Vouchfx.Cli/Vouchfx.Cli.csproj) from source at that revision.
#
# A full SHA is required, not a short SHA or a branch/tag name: a shallow
# `git fetch --depth 1 origin <ref>` only accepts a full SHA or a ref that the
# remote advertises: a short SHA is silently rejected by most git servers'
# shallow-fetch machinery, and pinning a moving branch name (e.g. "main")
# would defeat the point of a pin — reproducible builds and an auditable,
# reviewable upgrade step.
#
# If the SHA above is ever the all-zeros placeholder, bootstrap will
# refuse to run against it. The orchestrator stamps the real engine SHA here
# as part of standing this repository up; from then on, advancing the pin is
# a deliberate, reviewed action (see below).
#
# When to advance it
# -------------------
# Bump this SHA when:
#   - a new vouchfx engine release or milestone lands that the samples should
#     track (e.g. a new Sprint/Milestone merges to the engine's main branch);
#   - a sample needs an engine fix or a new provider that only exists past
#     the current pin;
#   - the engine's v1.x SDK contract freeze advances and this repo should
#     validate against the new baseline.
#
# How to advance it
# ------------------
#   1. Pick the new engine commit (a merge commit on tomas-rampas/vouchfx main
#      is usually the right choice — record its full 40-char SHA, not a
#      branch name).
#   2. Replace the SHA on the first line of this file with the new one.
#   3. Delete any local .vouchfx-src/ checkout (scripts/bootstrap.* will
#      re-fetch it) and re-run `scripts/run-sample.* all` to confirm every
#      sample still passes against the new pin.
#   4. Open a PR with just the pin bump (plus any sample changes the new
#      engine revision requires) so the change is reviewable in isolation.
#
# Once the vouchfx engine publishes a versioned NuGet package / GitHub
# release for the CLI, this file's role shifts from "commit to build from
# source" to "minimum supported engine version" — see docs/RUNNING.md.
